Two children were killed and eleven other people sustained injuries following a collision between a light motor vehicle and taxi at the Snel and Scott road intersection in Rustenburg North. On arrival, paramedics found numerous children lying around the taxi. “Paramedics discovered the bodies of two children, believed to be aged between six and eight, lying near the taxi. Unfortunately, they were declared dead,” ER24 said in a statement. Eleven other children were found to have sustained moderate injuries and were transported to a nearby hospital for further treatment. The cause of the accident is still unknown. -TNA Reporter